{"questionId":"28002","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A company makes doors for kitchen cupboards from two layers. The inside layer is wood,&nbsp;and its thickness is normally distributed with mean <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>mm</mtext></math> and standard deviation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>mm</mtext></math>.&nbsp;The outside layer is plastic, and its thickness is normally distributed with mean <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>mm</mtext></math> and&nbsp;standard deviation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>mm</mtext></math>. The thickness of the plastic is independent of the thickness of&nbsp;the wood.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Eight doors are to be packed into a box to send to a customer. The width of the box is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>82</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>mm</mtext></math>.&nbsp;The thickness of each door is independent.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the probability that the total thickness of the eight doors is greater than the width&nbsp;of the box.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>E</mtext><mfenced><mi>T</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>80</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Var</mtext><mfenced><mi>T</mi></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1156</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9248</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>~</mo><mtext>N</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mn>80</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9248</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>82</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0188</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0187753</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"28002","referenceCode":"22N.2.AHL.TZ0.6b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the probability that the total thickness of the eight doors is greater than the width of the box.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.14—Linear transformation of a single RV, E(X) and VAR(X), unbiased estimators","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.15—Central limit theorem"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}